ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I wouldn't recommend it to a student who is not supposed to pass the metrics requirement
A course worth taking only because you can kill two grad requirement birds with one stone.
I would recommend it but not strongly. If you really want to experience each field in a glance, it is a very nice introductory course. Otherwise, it may not be that interesting.
A good course for the big picture of empirical research.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Not much. I didn't learn how to apply topics but I know where I can start looking in case I need it
It broadened my understanding of general empirical research and empirical economics.
It helps a lot.Especially the last part.
